import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.datasets import load_wine
from pandas.plotting import radviz

#    
wine = load_wine()
dfData = pd.DataFrame(data=wine.data, columns=wine.feature_names)

#   
dfData['target'] = wine.target

#   (   'target'  dfData)
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_df = dfData.copy()  #  ,     
scaled_df[scaled_df.columns[:-1]] = scaler.fit_transform(scaled_df[scaled_df.columns[:-1]])

#  :  RadViz
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
radviz(scaled_df, 'target')
plt.title('RadViz   ')
plt.show()

#     
grouped_df = dfData.groupby('target').mean()
grouped_df['target'] = grouped_df.index  #   'target'   

#  :  RadViz
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
radviz(grouped_df, 'target')
plt.title('RadViz   ')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.datasets import load_wine
from pandas.plotting import andrews_curves

#    
wine = load_wine()
dfData = pd.DataFrame(data=wine.data, columns=wine.feature_names)

#   
dfData['target'] = wine.target

#  
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_df = dfData.copy()  #  ,     
scaled_df[scaled_df.columns[:-1]] = scaler.fit_transform(scaled_df[scaled_df.columns[:-1]])

#  :   
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
andrews_curves(scaled_df, 'target')
plt.title('    ')
plt.show()

#     
grouped_df = dfData.groupby('target').mean()
grouped_df['target'] = grouped_df.index  #   'target'   

#  :   
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
andrews_curves(grouped_df, 'target')
plt.title('    ')
plt.show()
